11#ifndef VIDEO_CALL_STATS2_H_
12#define VIDEO_CALL_STATS2_H_
13
14#include <list>
15#include <memory>
16
17#include "api/units/timestamp.h"
18#include "modules/include/module_common_types.h"
19#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/rtp_rtcp_defines.h"
20#include "rtc_base/constructor_magic.h"
21#include "rtc_base/task_queue.h"
22#include "rtc_base/task_utils/pending_task_safety_flag.h"
23#include "rtc_base/task_utils/repeating_task.h"
24#include "system_wrappers/include/clock.h"
25
26namespace webrtc {
27namespace internal {
28
29class CallStats {
30 public:
31 // Time interval for updating the observers.
32 static constexpr TimeDelta kUpdateInterval = TimeDelta::Millis(1000);
33
34 // Must be created and destroyed on the same task_queue.
35 CallStats(Clock* clock, TaskQueueBase* task_queue);
36 ~CallStats();
37
38 // Ensure that necessary repeating tasks are started.
39 void EnsureStarted();
40
41 // Expose an RtcpRttStats implementation without inheriting from RtcpRttStats.
42 // That allows us to separate the threading model of how RtcpRttStats is
43 // used (mostly on a process thread) and how CallStats is used (mostly on
44 // the TQ/worker thread). Since for both cases, there is a LastProcessedRtt()
45 // method, this separation allows us to not need a lock for either.
46 RtcpRttStats* AsRtcpRttStats() { return &rtcp_rtt_stats_impl_; }
47
48 // Registers/deregisters a new observer to receive statistics updates.
49 // Must be called from the construction thread.
50 void RegisterStatsObserver(CallStatsObserver* observer);
51 void DeregisterStatsObserver(CallStatsObserver* observer);
52
53 // Expose |LastProcessedRtt()| from RtcpRttStats to the public interface, as
54 // it is the part of the API that is needed by direct users of CallStats.
55 int64_t LastProcessedRtt() const;
56
57 // Exposed for tests to test histogram support.
58 void UpdateHistogramsForTest() { UpdateHistograms(); }
59
60 // Helper struct keeping track of the time a rtt value is reported.
61 struct RttTime {
62 RttTime(int64_t new_rtt, int64_t rtt_time) : rtt(new_rtt), time(rtt_time) {}
63 const int64_t rtt;
64 const int64_t time;
65 };
66
67 private:
68 // Part of the RtcpRttStats implementation. Called by RtcpRttStatsImpl.
69 void OnRttUpdate(int64_t rtt);
70
71 void UpdateAndReport();
72
73 // This method must only be called when the process thread is not
74 // running, and from the construction thread.
75 void UpdateHistograms();
76
77 class RtcpRttStatsImpl : public RtcpRttStats {
78 public:
79 explicit RtcpRttStatsImpl(CallStats* owner) : owner_(owner) {}
80 ~RtcpRttStatsImpl() override = default;
81
82 private:
83 void OnRttUpdate(int64_t rtt) override {
84 // For video send streams (video/video_send_stream.cc), the RtpRtcp module
85 // is currently created on a transport worker TaskQueue and not the worker
86 // thread - which is what happens in other cases. We should probably fix
87 // that so that the call consistently comes in on the right thread.
88 owner_->OnRttUpdate(rtt);
89 }
90
91 int64_t LastProcessedRtt() const override {
92 // This call path shouldn't be used anymore. This impl is only for
93 // propagating the rtt from the RtpRtcp module, which does not call
94 // LastProcessedRtt(). Down the line we should consider removing
95 // LastProcessedRtt() and use the interface for event notifications only.
96 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "Legacy call path";
97 return 0;
98 }
99
100 CallStats* const owner_;
101 } rtcp_rtt_stats_impl_{this};
102
103 Clock* const clock_;
104
105 // Used to regularly call UpdateAndReport().
106 RepeatingTaskHandle repeating_task_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
107
108 // The last RTT in the statistics update (zero if there is no valid estimate).
109 int64_t max_rtt_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
110
111 // Last reported average RTT value.
112 int64_t avg_rtt_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
113
114 int64_t sum_avg_rtt_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
115 int64_t num_avg_rtt_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
116 int64_t time_of_first_rtt_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
117
118 // All Rtt reports within valid time interval, oldest first.
119 std::list<RttTime> reports_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
120
121 // Observers getting stats reports.
122 std::list<CallStatsObserver*> observers_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(task_queue_);
123
124 TaskQueueBase* const task_queue_;
125
126 // Used to signal destruction to potentially pending tasks.
127 ScopedTaskSafety task_safety_;
128
129 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(CallStats);
130};
131
132} // namespace internal
133} // namespace webrtc
134
135#endif // VIDEO_CALL_STATS2_H_
